body:
The following code should generate an error:

```
module test(i_clk, o_reg);
   input wire i_clk;
   output wire o_reg;

  initial o_reg = 1'b0;
   always @(posedge i_clk)
      o_reg <= !o_reg;
endmodule
```

At issue is the fact that o_reg is a wire and not a register, therefore you should not be able to give it a value as though it were a register within an always block,

Dan

